result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant David G Weber in court with attorney Matthew J Pribyl.  Defendant David G Weber in custody.  Colleen Catherine Nordin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Minute sheet. State moves to dismiss but read in charge upon a plea in 17-CM-5. Court so orders, dismisses charge but reads in for sentencing purposes. Bond is no longer in effect.

Defendant David G Weber in court with attorney Matthew J Pribyl.  Defendant David G Weber in custody.  Colleen Catherine Nordin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court reviews events in file.  State will get a global offer to defense to resolve both cases. Atty Pribyl requests a status as soon the court's calendar allows. Bond remains in effect.  Status conference scheduled for January 12, 2017 at 08:00 am.

Defendant David G Weber appears by phone along with attorney Matthew J Pribyl who appears in person.  Raymond Pelrine appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court reviews events in file, questions defendant on phone appearance. Defendant indicates he didn't have a ride, tried walking but it was too cold. Atty Pribyl asks court to reschedule matter. Court reschedules matter. Bond remains in effect.  Status conference scheduled for January 5, 2017 at 11:15 am.

Defendant David G Weber in court with attorney Matthew J Pribyl.  Joan M. Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court reviews events in file. Atty Pribyl needs time to go through discovery with defendant, indicates defendant would like about 6 weeks to prepay financial obligations.  State has no objection to adjournment. Bond remains in effect.  Status conference scheduled for December 19, 2016 at 08:30 am.

Defendant David G Weber in court with attorney Matthew J Pribyl.  Raymond Pelrine appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court reviews events in file.  Atty Pribyl met with defendant for the first time this morning, indicates defendant would like to resolve matter as soon as possible. Defense requests a 2 week adjournment to further discuss matter with defendant. State has no objection. Bond remains in effect.  Plea hearing scheduled for October 10, 2016 at 11:00 am.
Maintain absolute sobriety from alcohol.  Fingerprints and photographs by Law Enforcement within 10 days.
